Description: Up for grabs is a nice starter 7 string guitar from Dean, the Dean Vendetta. This guitar sounds surprisingly good for the price, scoop it up and get learnin' 7-string guitar! Any guitarist looking to enter the realm of 7 strings will appreciate the Vendetta 1.7 electric guitar. With its extra bottom string tuned to a low B, here's an inexpensive ticket to a new world of deeper guitar sounds. It has a basswood top and body that sustains well with less weight. The full-scale bolt-on maple C shaped neck is easy to play with its rosewood fingerboard and pearl dot inlays. Features 24 frets, 1 volume, 1 tone, and 3-way pickup selector switch. If you're looking for your first 7-string rock guitar with dark, double humbucker sound or you're looking for a great backup axe, here it is.
